    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-12-04T17:14:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-12-04T17:14:00-05:00" n="1041"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1041">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">774.5 <gloss target="#t_MSP1">MSP</gloss>/11–2152:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1041<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Egypt</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d1041fn1">Repeated to London as telegram 3755.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-12-04T17:14:00-05:00"
                            >December 4, 1952—5:14 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1160. Re Emb <gloss target="#t_desp1">desp</gloss> 982 Nov 21<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d1041fn2">Not printed.</note> Dept hopes you will point out to Egypt
                    Govt that until such time as notes exchanged in accordance Dept A139 Oct 15 we
                    cannot complete formalities re equipment listed <gloss target="#t_Deptel1"
                        >Deptel</gloss> 1070<note n="3" xml:id="d1041fn3">See <ref
                            target="#d1033fn3">footnote 3, Document 1033</ref>.</note> Nov 21. Since
                    development overall program and therefore our reply to <persName
                        corresp="#p_NGM1">Naguib</persName>’s memo of Nov 10 may take some time we
                    wld hope that during interim at least police equipment wld move. We wld
                    therefore urge that Egypt Govt sign short form agreement now. It shld be pointed
                    out that our reply to <persName corresp="#p_NGM1">Naguib</persName> Nov 10 memo
                    will also depend to some extent upon receipt Annex II.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_AD1">
                            <hi rend="strong">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                            </hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
